036@SuppressWarnings({
037    "PMD.DataClass",
038    "PMD.FieldNamingConventions"
039})
040@MetaschemaAssembly(
041    formalName = "Inline Assembly Definition",
042    name = "inline-define-assembly",
043    moduleClass = MetaschemaModelModule.class)
044public class InlineDefineAssembly implements IBoundObject {
045  private final IMetaschemaData __metaschemaData;
046
047  @BoundFlag(
048      formalName = "Inline Assembly Name",
049      name = "name",
050      required = true,
051      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class)
052  private String _name;
053
054  @BoundFlag(
055      formalName = "Inline Assembly Binary Name",
056      name = "index",
057      typeAdapter = PositiveIntegerAdapter.class)
058  private BigInteger _index;
059
060  @BoundFlag(
061      formalName = "Deprecated Version",
062      name = "deprecated",
063      typeAdapter = StringAdapter.class)
064  private String _deprecated;
065
066  @BoundFlag(
067      formalName = "Minimum Occurrence",
068      name = "min-occurs",
069      defaultValue = "0",
070      typeAdapter = NonNegativeIntegerAdapter.class)
071  private BigInteger _minOccurs;
072
073  @BoundFlag(
074      formalName = "Maximum Occurrence",
075      name = "max-occurs",
076      defaultValue = "1",
077      typeAdapter = StringAdapter.class,
078      valueConstraints = @ValueConstraints(
079          matches = @Matches(level = IConstraint.Level.ERROR, pattern = "^[1-9][0-9]*|unbounded$")))
080  private String _maxOccurs;
081
082  @BoundField(
083      formalName = "Formal Name",
084      description = "A formal name for the data construct, to be presented in documentation.",
085      useName = "formal-name")
086  private String _formalName;
087
088  @BoundField(
089      formalName = "Description",
090      description = "A short description of the data construct's purpose, describing the constructs semantics.",
091      useName = "description",
092      typeAdapter = MarkupLineAdapter.class)
093  private MarkupLine _description;
094
095  @BoundAssembly(
096      formalName = "Property",
097      useName = "prop",
098      maxOccurs = -1,
099      groupAs = @GroupAs(name = "props", inJson = JsonGroupAsBehavior.LIST))
100  private List<Property> _props;
101
102  @BoundAssembly(
103      formalName = "JSON Key",
104      description = "Used in JSON (and similar formats) to identify a flag that will be used as the property name in an object hold a collection of sibling objects. Requires that siblings must never share `json-key` values.",
105      useName = "json-key")
106  private JsonKey _jsonKey;
107
108  @BoundAssembly(
109      formalName = "Group As",
110      useName = "group-as")
111  private GroupingAs _groupAs;
112
113  @BoundChoiceGroup(
114      maxOccurs = -1,
115      assemblies = {
116          @BoundGroupedAssembly(formalName = "Inline Flag Definition", useName = "define-flag",
117              binding = InlineDefineFlag.class),
118          @BoundGroupedAssembly(formalName = "Flag Reference", useName = "flag", binding = FlagReference.class)
119      },
120      groupAs = @GroupAs(name = "flags", inJson = JsonGroupAsBehavior.LIST))
121  private List<Object> _flags;
122
123  @BoundAssembly(
124      useName = "model")
125  private AssemblyModel _model;
126
127  @BoundAssembly(
128      useName = "constraint")
129  private AssemblyConstraints _constraint;
130
131  @BoundField(
132      formalName = "Remarks",
133      description = "Any explanatory or helpful information to be provided about the remarks parent.",
134      useName = "remarks")
135  private Remarks _remarks;
136
137  @BoundAssembly(
138      formalName = "Example",
139      useName = "example",
140      maxOccurs = -1,
141      groupAs = @GroupAs(name = "examples", inJson = JsonGroupAsBehavior.LIST))
142  private List<Example> _examples;

170    _index = value;
171  }
172

174    return _deprecated;
175  }

178    _deprecated = value;

187  }

190    return _maxOccurs;

194    _maxOccurs = value;

214    return _props;
215  }
216

218    _props = value;
219  }
220
221  /**
222   * Add a new {@link Property} item to the underlying collection.
223   *
224   * @param item
225   *          the item to add
226   * @return {@code true}
227   */
228  public boolean addProp(Property item) {
229    Property value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
230    if (_props == null) {
231      _props = new LinkedList<>();
232    }
233    return _props.add(value);
234  }
235
236  /**
237   * Remove the first matching {@link Property} item from the underlying
238   * collection.
239   *
240   * @param item
241   *          the item to remove
242   * @return {@code true} if the item was removed or {@code false} otherwise
243   */
244  public boolean removeProp(Property item) {
245    Property value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
246    return _props != null && _props.remove(value);
247  }

250    return _jsonKey;
251  }

254    _jsonKey = value;

302    _examples = value;
303  }
304
305  /**
306   * Add a new {@link Example} item to the underlying collection.
307   *
308   * @param item
309   *          the item to add
310   * @return {@code true}
311   */
312  public boolean addExample(Example item) {
313    Example value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
314    if (_examples == null) {
315      _examples = new LinkedList<>();
316    }
317    return _examples.add(value);
318  }
319
320  /**
321   * Remove the first matching {@link Example} item from the underlying
322   * collection.
323   *
324   * @param item
325   *          the item to remove
326   * @return {@code true} if the item was removed or {@code false} otherwise
327   */
328  public boolean removeExample(Example item) {
329    Example value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
330    return _examples != null && _examples.remove(value);
331  }
